HEADWORD: Sursum corda
<hw>Sur"sum cor"da</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L. <ets>sursum</ets>
upward + <ets>corda</ets> hearts.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>In the
Eucharist, the versicles immediately before the preface, inviting the
people to join in the service by ⟦ldquo⟧lifting up the heart⟦rdquo⟧ to
God.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

